title: Febuwhump Wrap-Up 2/2
body:
The last Febuwhump drabble is now up! 

It’s been a really fun month writing all of these drabbles, I haven’t written this much in a month in…probably a few years, and this has proven to me that I’m still capable of it. Thanks to @spidersonangst for organising this event!

Part 1

Day 15 - Betrayal 

Fandom - Critical Role

Summary - “Caleb.” Master Ikithon’s voice interrupted his thoughts. “They are not your friends. They are traitors to the Empire and they must be dealt with accordingly. So deal with them.”


Day 16 - Car Crash

Fandom - Stargate Atlantis

Summary - “What in god’s name happened to your face?”


Day 17 - Heartbreak

Fandom - Fantastic Beasts and Where to Find Them

Summary - Leta Lestrange, the love of his life, was dead.


Day 18 - Damage

Fandom - Marvel Cinematic Universe

Summary - Changing back was always incredibly painful for Bruce, but never like this. Never so localised, never so excruciating and never so real. Of course, normally injuries would be healed by the time he woke up.


Day 19 - Breach

Fandom - The Losers (2010)

Summary -  Sometimes Cougar had to wonder if he and his team would ever be safe again. If they would ever be able to settle down without having to look over their shoulders every single day for the rest of their lives. He wondered if it was even possible. And he wondered if he even wanted it.


Day 20 - Time Travel

Fandom - Critical Role

Summary -  Almost every night in his dreams, Caleb went back in time. He went back to his childhood, back to Ikithon, but more often than not, he went back to his parents.


Day 21 - Insomnia

Fandom - Voltron: Legendary Defender

Summary -  Matt never thought he would miss his cold, cramped cell. He never thought he’d miss the hard floor, dull lighting and absolute, never-ending silence. But now, bundled up in several soft blankets on what could easily be the most comfortable bed in the entire universe, he found himself wanting all of that back.


Day 22 - Regret

Fandom - The Musketeers (BBC)

Summary - "Just…just wait in the car, alright? We’ll be back soon but you need to stay here. Alright?“

There was no time to consider that head injury or not, this was Aramis and he wasn’t just going to sit in the car and wait. He’d never been that kind of person.


Day 23 - Addiction

Fandom - Stargate Atlantis

Summary -  Rodney would never admit it to himself, but everyone around him knew just as he did that he had a problem. A problem he refused to call a problem, a problem that no one else seemed up for addressing, but a problem nonetheless.


Day 24 - Blood Lust

Fandom - Stargate Atlantis

Summary -  Rodney was sure that his body was on fire. It had to be, there was no other explanation for the excruciating pain which ran through his veins, intensifying with every heartbeat until he was writhing on the floor clawing at his arms and screaming for it to stop.


Day 25 - Battlefield

Fandom - Marvel Cinematic Universe

Summary -  This pain…he’d felt it before, not nearly as often but enough that he knew what had caused it.

It was the pain which came when Hulk was defeated.


Day 26 - Shot

Fandom - Marvel Cinematic Universe

Summary - Tony didn’t scream as the bullet tore through his shoulder, but it was a close thing.


Day 27 - Asylum

Fandom - Stargate Atlantis

Summary -  They came in the night, carrying ropes for his limbs and cloth to stuff between his teeth. Rodney was so deeply asleep that he had no chance to fight, no chance to even try to escape.


Day 28 - Suicide

Fandom - Final Fantasy XV

Summary -  “Have you ever thought about killing yourself?” Prompto had asked once, after they’d both had too much to drink at a gala and decided to hide out in a coat closet.
